# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SolBeat — environment variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values you need. The app
# is designed to degrade gracefully: missing optional keys disable their
# feature instead of crashing the build. Only the [REQUIRED] vars are
# needed to boot the site with non-trivial functionality.
#
# Marker key:
#   [REQUIRED]  app loses a core feature without this value
#   [OPTIONAL]  feature degrades or no-ops, rest of the site works
#
# ⚠️ NEXT_PUBLIC_ vars are bundled into client JS — only use for values
#    safe to expose to anyone who views the page source.
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ─── SOLANA DATA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# [OPTIONAL] Helius RPC API key. Used for getAccountInfo,
# getTokenAccountsByOwner, getSignaturesForAddress, and DAS. Without it
# the code falls back to api.mainnet-beta.solana.com which is heavily
# rate-limited and will time out under any meaningful traffic.
# Get one (free tier available): https://helius.dev
HELIUS_API_KEY=

# [OPTIONAL] Client-side Solana RPC URL. Used by the wallet adapter +
# any client component that needs to talk to the chain directly. Falls
# back to api.mainnet-beta.solana.com when empty.
# ⚠️ NEXT_PUBLIC_ — bundled into client JS. If you embed a Helius key
#    here, lock it down in the Helius dashboard with referrer
#    restrictions + rate limits before deploying.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SOLANA_RPC=https://mainnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=YOUR_HELIUS_KEY

# [OPTIONAL] Birdeye market data API. Used as an enrichment source for
# tokens that DexScreener doesn't index well. When missing, the app
# falls back to DexScreener for all market data.
# Get one (free tier available): https://birdeye.so/developers
BIRDEYE_API_KEY=

# [OPTIONAL] Jupiter swap API key for the paid api.jup.ag tier
# (higher rate limits, lower latency). When missing, the free
# lite-api.jup.ag is used — works for the swap flow with no caveats
# at hackathon-level traffic.
# Get one: https://station.jup.ag/docs/apis
JUPITER_API_KEY=


# ─── AI ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# [REQUIRED] Anthropic API key. Powers the AI Synthesis panel + risk
# scoring. Without it the synthesis panel renders empty and risk
# scoring falls back to a pure-TypeScript heuristic.
# Get one: https://console.anthropic.com
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# [OPTIONAL] Perplexity API key. Powers the live Catalysts panel
# (news + on-chain events from the last 24h). Without it, Catalysts
# renders empty.
# Get one: https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=


# ─── SOCIAL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# [OPTIONAL] twitterapi.io key. Pulls recent X posts about each token
# for the Recent Tweets panel + the social-sentiment input to AI
# synthesis. Without it, those features render empty / receive no
# tweet data.
# Get one: https://twitterapi.io
TWITTERAPI_IO_KEY=


# ─── CACHING (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────

# [OPTIONAL] Upstash Redis REST URL. Used to cache pulse snapshots,
# trending payloads, and AI outputs across requests. Without it, the
# app falls back to a per-process in-memory cache (works fine for
# single-instance deploys; matters once you scale horizontally).
# Get one: https://upstash.com/redis
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=

# [OPTIONAL] Companion token for the URL above. Both must be set for
# Redis to activate.
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=


# ─── FEE ACCOUNTS (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────

# [OPTIONAL] Block Valley treasury wallet (base58 Solana address).
# Receives the 5% reclaim fee when users close empty token accounts.
# Without it, the reclaim flow still executes but skips the fee
# transfer — users get 100% of the recovered SOL.
# ⚠️ NEXT_PUBLIC_ — this is a wallet address, safe to expose.
NEXT_PUBLIC_BV_TREASURY_WALLET=

# [OPTIONAL] Jupiter swap referral account (base58 Solana address).
# Earns the SolBeat platform fee on each swap routed through the in-app
# trade flow. Without it, swaps work normally with no platform fee.
# ⚠️ NEXT_PUBLIC_ — this is a wallet address, safe to expose.
# Set one up: https://referral.jup.ag
NEXT_PUBLIC_JUPITER_REFERRAL_ACCOUNT=


# ─── AI PROMPTS (proprietary) ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These three env vars hold the system prompts that drive SolBeat's
# AI features. They are kept out of source so this open-source repo
# does not ship Block Valley Labs' prompt-engineering work.
#
# Behavior when missing:
#   - CLAUDE_SYSTEM_PROMPT_TOKEN_ANALYSIS missing → AI Synthesis
#     panel returns null, UI shows "AI synthesis unavailable"
#   - CLAUDE_SYSTEM_PROMPT_RISK_SCORE missing → risk scoring falls
#     back to the pure-TypeScript heuristic baseline (still useful)
#   - PERPLEXITY_SYSTEM_PROMPT_CATALYSTS missing → Catalysts panel
#     renders empty
#
# Multi-line values are supported inside double quotes; newlines are
# preserved by Next's @next/env loader.

# [REQUIRED if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY set]
# Proprietary Block Valley reasoning prompt. Not included in this
# repo. Write your own or contact admin@blockvalley.io for licensing.
CLAUDE_SYSTEM_PROMPT_TOKEN_ANALYSIS=

# [OPTIONAL] (heuristic baseline used if missing)
# Proprietary Block Valley reasoning prompt. Not included in this
# repo. Write your own or contact admin@blockvalley.io for licensing.
CLAUDE_SYSTEM_PROMPT_RISK_SCORE=

# [REQUIRED if PERPLEXITY_API_KEY set]
# Proprietary Block Valley reasoning prompt. Not included in this
# repo. Write your own or contact admin@blockvalley.io for licensing.
PERPLEXITY_SYSTEM_PROMPT_CATALYSTS=
